Argued and submitted December 20, 1983, In the Matter of the Compensation of Jonathan Wallace, Claimant. WALLACE, Petitioner, v. INDUSTRIAL INDEMNITY COMPANY et al, Respondents. (81-11546; CA A28285) 680 P2d 726 Ronald L. Bohy, Salem, argued the cause for petitioner. On the brief was Linda C. Love, Salem. Marshall C. Cheney, Jr., Portland, argued the cause for respondents. With him on the brief was Ridgway K. Foley, Jr., Portland, P.C. Before Gillette, Presiding Judge, and Van Hoomissen and Young, Judges. PER CURIAM

reversed and remanded May 9, 1984
